    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 28.14,
      "end": 29.98,
      "text": "Recording by Kristen Luoma.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 29.98,
      "end": 35.08,
      "text": "There was once a dog who used to snap at people and bite them without any provocation,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 36.06,
      "end": 39.26,
      "text": "and who was a great nuisance to everyone who came to his master's house.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 40.06,
      "end": 45.0,
      "text": "So his master fastened a bell round his neck to warn people of his prisons.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 45.94,
      "end": 50.8,
      "text": "The dog was very proud of the bell and strutted about tinkling it with immense satisfaction.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 51.9,
      "end": 54.68,
      "text": "But an old dog came up to him and said,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 55.74,
      "end": 58.46,
      "text": "Fewer heirs you give yourself the better, my friend.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 59.32,
      "end": 63.4,
      "text": "You don't think, do you, that your bell was given you as a reward of merit?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 64.32,
      "end": 67.22,
      "text": "On the contrary, it is a badge of disgrace.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 70.36,
      "end": 72.96,
      "text": "Notariety is often mistaken for fame.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 75.56,
      "end": 77.34,
      "text": "End of the mischief's dog.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
